Genomic epidemiology and bioinformatics webinars and trainings
Scroll through trainings here or you can download the whole table as a .csv file by clicking the download button at the bottom of the table. You can also view a full-sized version here and easily group and filter to find trainings of interest. Do you have a training to add? Fill out the form at the bottom of page or here!





Self-Study Exercises



Title
Description
Organizer




Digital Epidemiology Workshop
Hands on exercise using web-based tools (EpiCollect, Pathogenwatch, Data-flo, Microreact) to conduct a genomic epidemiology investigation.
Centre for Genomic Pathogen Surveillance


Infectious Disease Genomic Epidemiology 2023
This 4-day course from CBW provides an introduction to genomic epidemiology analysis followed by hands-on practical tutorials demonstrating the use of selected analysis tools. The tutorials are designed as self-contained units that include example data and detailed instructions for installation of all required bioinformatics tools or access to publicly available web applications.
Bioinformatics.ca


Whole genome multi locus sequence typing activity
This activity was developed by the New York Integrated Food Safety Center of Excellence to provide public health staff or students of public health with an understanding of how whole genome sequencing (WGS), and particularly whole genome multi locus sequence typing (wgMLST), works as a subtyping method. The activity can be taken individually or in group (3-5 people per group suggested).
New York Food Safety Center of Excellence/ Cornell University





Other resources for genomic epidemiology in public health


An applied genomic epidemiological handbook. by Alli Black and Gytis Dudas, freely available online here, and available in print here.
Wellcome Connecting Science offers a variety of genomics and bioinformatics courses through FutureLearn




